columns.name: sql_data_access
columns.column_type_utf8: enum('CONTAINS SQL','NO SQL','READS SQL DATA','MODIFIES SQL DATA')

dd_object.name: time_zone_leap_second
dd_object.comment: Leap seconds information for time zones

columns.name: Number_of_lines
columns.comment: Number of lines in the file or rows in the table. Used to version table definitions.

columns.name: Relay_log_name
columns.comment: The name of the current relay log file.

columns.name: Relay_log_pos
columns.comment: The relay log position of the last executed event.

columns.name: Master_log_name
columns.comment: The name of the master binary log file from which the events in the relay log file were read.

columns.name: Master_log_pos
columns.comment: The master log position of the last executed event.

columns.name: Sql_delay
columns.comment: The number of seconds that the slave must lag behind the master.

columns.name: Id
columns.comment: Internal Id that uniquely identifies this record.

columns.name: Channel_name
columns.comment: The channel on which the replica is connected to a source. Used in Multisource Replication

columns.name: Privilege_checks_username
columns.comment: Username part of PRIVILEGE_CHECKS_USER.

columns.name: Privilege_checks_hostname
columns.comment: Hostname part of PRIVILEGE_CHECKS_USER.

columns.name: Require_row_format
columns.comment: Indicates whether the channel shall only accept row based events.

columns.name: Require_table_primary_key_check
columns.comment: Indicates what is the channel policy regarding tables having primary keys on create and alter table queries

columns.name: Assign_gtids_to_anonymous_transactions_type
columns.comment: Indicates whether the channel will generate a new GTID for anonymous transactions. OFF means that anonymous transactions will remain anonymous. LOCAL means that anonymous transactions will be assigned a newly generated GTID based on server_uuid. UUID indicates that anonymous transactions will be assigned a newly generated GTID based on Assign_gtids_to_anonymous_transactions_value

columns.name: Assign_gtids_to_anonymous_transactions_value
columns.comment: Indicates the UUID used while generating GTIDs for anonymous transactions

columns.name: Number_of_lines
columns.comment: Number of lines in the file.

columns.name: Master_log_name
columns.comment: The name of the master binary log currently being read from the master.

columns.name: Master_log_pos
columns.comment: The master log position of the last read event.

columns.name: Host
columns.comment: The host name of the source.

columns.name: User_name
columns.comment: The user name used to connect to the master.

columns.name: User_password
columns.comment: The password used to connect to the master.

columns.name: Port
columns.comment: The network port used to connect to the master.

columns.name: Connect_retry
columns.comment: The period (in seconds) that the slave will wait before trying to reconnect to the master.

columns.name: Enabled_ssl
columns.comment: Indicates whether the server supports SSL connections.

columns.name: Ssl_ca
columns.comment: The file used for the Certificate Authority (CA) certificate.

columns.name: Ssl_capath
columns.comment: The path to the Certificate Authority (CA) certificates.

columns.name: Ssl_cert
columns.comment: The name of the SSL certificate file.

columns.name: Ssl_cipher
columns.comment: The name of the cipher in use for the SSL connection.

columns.name: Ssl_key
columns.comment: The name of the SSL key file.

columns.name: Ssl_verify_server_cert
columns.comment: Whether to verify the server certificate.

columns.name: Bind
columns.comment: Displays which interface is employed when connecting to the MySQL server

columns.name: Ignored_server_ids
columns.comment: The number of server IDs to be ignored, followed by the actual server IDs

columns.name: Uuid
columns.comment: The master server uuid.

columns.name: Retry_count
columns.comment: Number of reconnect attempts, to the master, before giving up.

columns.name: Ssl_crl
columns.comment: The file used for the Certificate Revocation List (CRL)

columns.name: Ssl_crlpath
columns.comment: The path used for Certificate Revocation List (CRL) files

columns.name: Enabled_auto_position
columns.comment: Indicates whether GTIDs will be used to retrieve events from the master.

columns.name: Channel_name
columns.comment: The channel on which the replica is connected to a source. Used in Multisource Replication

columns.name: Tls_version
columns.comment: Tls version

columns.name: Public_key_path
columns.comment: The file containing public key of master server.

columns.name: Get_public_key
columns.comment: Preference to get public key from master.

columns.name: Network_namespace
columns.comment: Network namespace used for communication with the master server.

columns.name: Master_compression_algorithm
columns.comment: Compression algorithm supported for data transfer between source and replica.

columns.name: Master_zstd_compression_level
columns.comment: Compression level associated with zstd compression algorithm.

columns.name: Tls_ciphersuites
columns.comment: Ciphersuites used for TLS 1.3 communication with the master server.

columns.name: Source_connection_auto_failover
columns.comment: Indicates whether the channel connection failover is enabled.

columns.name: Gtid_only
columns.comment: Indicates if this channel only uses GTIDs and does not persist positions.

columns.name: Channel_name
columns.comment: The channel on which the replica is connected to a source. Used in Multisource Replication

columns.name: source_uuid
columns.comment: uuid of the source where the transaction was originally executed.

columns.name: interval_start
columns.comment: First number of interval.

columns.name: interval_end
columns.comment: Last number of interval.

columns.name: Channel_name
columns.comment: The replication channel name that connects source and replica.

columns.name: Host
columns.comment: The source hostname that the replica will attempt to switch over the replication connection to in case of a failure.

columns.name: Port
columns.comment: The source port that the replica will attempt to switch over the replication connection to in case of a failure.

columns.name: Network_namespace
columns.comment: The source network namespace that the replica will attempt to switch over the replication connection to in case of a failure. If its value is empty, connections use the default (global) namespace.

columns.name: Weight
columns.comment: The order in which the replica shall try to switch the connection over to when there are failures. Weight can be set to a number between 1 and 100, where 100 is the highest weight and 1 the lowest.

columns.name: Managed_name
columns.comment: The name of the group which this server belongs to.

columns.name: Channel_name
columns.comment: The replication channel name that connects source and replica.

columns.name: Managed_name
columns.comment: The name of the source which needs to be managed.

columns.name: Managed_type
columns.comment: Determines the managed type.

columns.name: Configuration
columns.comment: The data to help manage group. For Managed_type = GroupReplication, Configuration value should contain {"Primary_weight": 80, "Secondary_weight": 60}, so that it assigns weight=80 to PRIMARY of the group, and weight=60 for rest of the members in mysql.replication_asynchronous_connection_failover table.

columns.name: name
columns.comment: The action name.

columns.name: event
columns.comment: The event that will trigger the action.

columns.name: enabled
columns.comment: Whether the action is enabled.

columns.name: type
columns.comment: The action type.

columns.name: priority
columns.comment: The order on which the action will be run, value between 1 and 100, lower values first.

columns.name: error_handling
columns.comment: On errors during the action will be handled: IGNORE, CRITICAL.

columns.name: name
columns.comment: The configuration name.

columns.name: version
columns.comment: The version of the configuration name.

columns.name: default_value
columns.generation_expression: (case `cost_name` when _utf8mb4'disk_temptable_create_cost' then 20.0 when _utf8mb4'disk_temptable_row_cost' then 0.5 when _utf8mb4'key_compare_cost' then 0.05 when _utf8mb4'memory_temptable_create_cost' then 1.0 when _utf8mb4'memory_temptable_row_cost' then 0.1 when _utf8mb4'row_evaluate_cost' then 0.1 else NULL end)
columns.generation_expression_utf8: (case `cost_name` when _utf8mb4\'disk_temptable_create_cost\' then 20.0 when _utf8mb4\'disk_temptable_row_cost\' then 0.5 when _utf8mb4\'key_compare_cost\' then 0.05 when _utf8mb4\'memory_temptable_create_cost\' then 1.0 when _utf8mb4\'memory_temptable_row_cost\' then 0.1 when _utf8mb4\'row_evaluate_cost\' then 0.1 else NULL end)

columns.name: default_value
columns.generation_expression: (case `cost_name` when _utf8mb4'io_block_read_cost' then 1.0 when _utf8mb4'memory_block_read_cost' then 0.25 else NULL end)
columns.generation_expression_utf8: (case `cost_name` when _utf8mb4\'io_block_read_cost\' then 1.0 when _utf8mb4\'memory_block_read_cost\' then 0.25 else NULL end)
